    <hr>

    <h3>Why is this safer?</h3>
    <p>
        Using <b>htmlspecialchars($_SERVER["PHP_SELF"])</b> prevents Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks.
        It ensures that malicious scripts cannot be injected through the URL or form action.
        Without it, attackers could manipulate the form action and execute harmful code.
    </p>

